        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>This braised duck is another dish sel­dom found in Per­anakan restau­rants, and a good choice if you are not hav­ing any other poul­try dishes.</p>
    <p>Best eaten with rice, its in­tense flavour comes from a blend of spices and soya sauce used to sim­mer the bird un­til its meat turns fork-ten­der. There is no chilli, giv­ing it a dif­fer­ent flavour pro­file from other stewed-meat items on the menu.</p>

